    <briefdescription>
<para>Container for type-erased component lifecycle function pointers. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>`ComponentOps` enables runtime invocation of component lifecycle hooks without knowing the concrete component type. Function pointers are set during type registration via `ComponentReflector::registerType&lt;T&gt;()`.</para>
<para>## Type Erasure Pattern</para>
<para>```cpp // At registration (type known): <ref refid="structhelios_1_1ecs_1_1types_1_1ComponentOps" kindref="compound">ComponentOps</ref> ops{ .onAcquire = [](void* ptr) { static_cast&lt;HealthComponent*&gt;(ptr)-&gt;<ref refid="structhelios_1_1ecs_1_1types_1_1ComponentOps_1afa07459f0e01dd5ccc20366bdadb126a" kindref="member">onAcquire()</ref>; } };</para>
<para>// At runtime (type erased): if (ops.onAcquire) { ops.onAcquire(rawComponent); } ```</para>
<para><simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1ecs_1_1ComponentOpsRegistry" kindref="compound">ComponentOpsRegistry</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1ecs_1_1ComponentReflector" kindref="compound">ComponentReflector</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para>Traits </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
